/* Override */
"Override With A Factor Of " = "按系数覆盖 ";

/* Description */
"Allows fat and protein to be converted into future carb equivalents using the Warsaw formula of kilocalories divided by 10.\n\nThis spreads the carb equivilants over a maximum duration setting that can be configured from 5-12 hours.\n\nDelay is time from now until the first future carb entry.\n\nInterval in minutes is how many minutes are between entries. The shorter the interval, the smoother the result. 10, 15, 20, 30, or 60 are reasonable choices.\n\nAdjustment factor is how much effect the fat and protein has on the entries. 1.0 is full effect (original Warsaw Method) and 0.5 is half effect. Note that you may find that your normal carb ratio needs to increase to a larger number if you begin adding fat and protein entries. For this reason, it is best to start with a factor of about 0.5 to ease into it.\n\nDefault settings: Time Cap: 8 h, Interval: 30 min, Factor: 0.5, Delay 60 min" = "允许使用 Warsaw 公式（千卡/10）将脂肪和蛋白质转换为未来碳水当量。\n\n碳水当量在最长持续时间内分散给出，可设置范围为 5–12 小时。\n\n延迟：从现在开始到第一次生成碳水数据的等待时间。\n\n间隔：每条数据之间的时间间隔。间隔越短，结果越平滑。10、15、20、30、60 分钟都是合理选项。\n\n调整系数表示脂肪与蛋白质对碳水当量影响的比例：1.0 为完全效果（原 Warsaw 方法），0.5 为一半效果。如果启用 FPU，你的碳水比可能需要提高，因此建议从 0.5 开始试用。\n\n默认设置：时间上限 8 小时，间隔 30 分钟，系数 0.5，延迟 60 分钟";

/* Fat/Protein additional info */
"\n\nCarb equivalents that get to small (0.6g or under) will be excluded and the equivalents over 0.6 but under 1 will be rounded up to 1. With a higher time interval setting you'll get fewer equivalents with a higher carb amount." = "\n\n低于 0.6g 的碳水当量会被忽略，0.6–1g 的会取整为 1g。若使用较大的间隔，条目更少但每条含量更高。";

